http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Tight-security-for-Paryaya-festival/article13989340.ece

Tight security will be in place at Udupi during the Paryaya festival on January 17 and 18.As it would be a historic Paryaya with Vishwesha Tirtha Swami of Pejawar Mutt ascending the Paryaya Peetha for a record fifth time at the 800-year-old Sri Krishna Mutt/Temple on January 18, a large number of people are expected to witness it.In a press release issued here, K. Annamalai, Superintendent of Police, said that besides eminent persons, lakhs of devotees were expected to arrive here for the festival. Therefore, tight police security would be arranged to check chain-snatching, pickpocket and other offences during the programme. Besides police personnel from Udupi district, police personnel from neighbouring districts would also be pressed into service during the festival. Five Deputy Superintendents of Poli0ce, 14 Circle Inspectors, two Reserve Police Inspectors, 45 sub-inspectors, 90 assistant sub-inspectors, 620 head constables and police constables, 80 women police and 284 home guards would be on security duty during the festival.In addition, six units of Karnataka State Reserve Police (KSRP) and six parties of District Armed Reserve Police would be pressed into service. Six checkposts would be set up at vital locations to check untoward incidents and to check vehicles.A police outpost would be set up at the Car Street here for security purposes and also to provide information and help devotees. Already 21 places have been earmarked for temporary parking inner and outer zones of the city, the release said.